cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the deployment of UAVs as flying base stations for wireless communication. Hence, it is highly likely to belong to this category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the transmit power of UAVs while satisfying the users' rate requirements. This optimization problem can be related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the deployment of multiple UAVs and determining their optimal locations and cell boundaries. This can be related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper involves multiple UAVs acting as flying base stations. This can be related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves an optimization problem that can be modeled using game theory. Hence, it is possible for the paper to belong to this category as well.
